An all-female traffic officer roadblock is taking place along the N14  on Wednesday to highlight the gendered issues faced by officers. Courtesy of #DSTV403 JOHANNESBURG - An all-female traffic officer roadblock took place along the N14 on Wednesday. Officers from the JMPD, SAPS, Gauteng Traffic Police and the National Traffic Police participated in the demonstration. WATCH: JMPD investigating viral blood test video Gauteng's MEC for Community Safety Faith Mazibuko accompanied and addressed the officers. The operation was aimed at highlighting the struggles faced by female officers during operations, especially during Women's Month. READ: Joburg firefighters demand police escort for emergency calls Female officers have complained that motorists do not respect their position in authority. Mazibuko highlighted some of the challenges facing women officers, including inappropriate design and sizing of protective equipment and clothing.